{{ pc.standardSection('id="status"') }}
  <h3>Status</h3>
  <p>
    Web Portals is in <strong>draft specification</strong> phase. The primitives above represent the proposed API surface.
  </p>
  <h4 style="margin-top: 1rem;">Dependencies</h4>
  <ul style="font-size: 0.9rem;">
    <li><a href="/projects/webinjectors/">Web Injectors</a> — Provides the injector hierarchy that serves as the logical tree backbone</li>
    <li><a href="/projects/webcontexts/">Web Contexts</a> — Context resolution via logical ancestry</li>
    <li><a href="/projects/webdirectives/">Web Directives</a> — The <code>CustomTemplateDirective</code> base for the portal directive</li>
  </ul>
  <h4 style="margin-top: 1rem;">Resolved Questions</h4>
  <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-text-muted);">
    The four open questions that gated this protocol were ratified in
    <a href="/backlog/1000-ratify-the-web-portals-protocol-resolve-the-4-spec-open-ques/">backlog #1000</a>
    (2026-06-19):
  </p>
  <ul style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-text-muted);">
    <li><strong>logicalParent surface</strong> — a writable element-reference property (mirroring <code>popoverTargetElement</code>) reflecting a declarative <code>logicalparent="id"</code> attribute, with a validating setter + <code>logicalparentchange</code>. <em>Not</em> a method.</li>
    <li><strong>Logical bubbling × retargeting</strong> — a separate opt-in <code>composedLogical</code> flag + <code>composedLogicalPath()</code> (never an overload of native <code>composed</code>); <code>logicalPath</code> computed pre-retarget; the retarget host at a logical hop is the <em>declaration</em> element.</li>
    <li><strong>Focus scopes</strong> — struck as a portal primitive; the portal composes the <a href="/intents/focus-containment/">Focus Containment Intent</a>.</li>
    <li><strong>Deferred resolution</strong> — deferred-by-default (attach-or-observe via the shared <code>InjectorRoot</code> observer); structural diagnostic trigger (DOMContentLoaded / one <code>requestAnimationFrame</code>), with a <code>required</code> opt-out for fail-fast.</li>
  </ul>
{{ pc.endStandardSection() }}

